Chelsea host Ajax on Match Day 4 of the Champions League on Tuesday. Frank Lampard’s men snatched victory when both sides clashed in Amsterdam, with Michy Batshuayi scoring a late winner. The win, however, did not see Ajax relinquish leadership of Group H, ahead of the game at Stamford Bridge. Kick-off is 9 pm West African time. Tuesday, November 5 Full time: It ends 4-4 at Stamford Bridge. Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.